<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4"><tr bgcolor="#000000"><td><font color="#FFFFFF"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial" size="6">Black Discard</font></td></tr></table><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td></td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Author</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Sleepy</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Description</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Knock cards out of people&#39;s hands.  Bounce creatures back with key cards in deck.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Cards</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Lands:<br>
<br>
18 Swamps<br>
3 Sheltered Valley<br>
<br>
Black:<br>
<br>
4 x Pox<br>
4 x Hymn to Tourach<br>
4 x Funeral Charm<br>
4 x Megrim<br>
4 x Dark Ritual<br>
1 x Vamperic Tutor<br>
1 x Demonic Tutor<br>
2 x Dark Banishing<br>
3 x Oppression<br>
1 x Skeletal Scrying<br>
4 x Hypnotic Specter<br>
<br>
Artifacts:<br>
<br>
4 x Rack<br>
3 x Noetic Scale<br>
1 x Mox Jet<br>
<br>
Sideboard<br>
<br>
2 x Drain Life<br>
4 x Natuko Shade<br>
3 x Massacre<br>
3 x Braids, Cabal Minion<br>
3 x Underworld Dreams   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Use direct discards resources like the Hypnotic Specter, Hymns, and Funeral Charms to slow down the opponents as much as possible.  Use the searching devices, the tutors, to try to get the Oppression or Megrim as soon as possible.  Pox repeatedly to help knock down life and deprive them of land resources.  Normally the Pox and megrim will knock your opponent down to sufficient life to finish off your opponents in a matter of a few turns w/ racks or Underworld dreams.<br>
<br>
Sideboard if necessary.  For more artifact removal, there&#39;s the powder keg.  To put more punch in the deck, the Shades and even Braids.  Braids for more stall and resource deprival.  Underworld dreams to speed the damage in the deck.  Drain lifes to re adjust the numbers.<br>
<br>
This deck is a real numbers game and the main reason that it&#39;s listed/entered as an advanced deck is for the sheer annoyance of calculating life points in your head.  Otherwise it&#39;ll probably be listed as an Intermediate deck, even a fun deck. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
